President Muhammadu Buhari has approved a sum of N10billion intervention fund for upgrade of Akanu Ibiam International Airport, Enugu. The president who announced the approval in a statement on Thursday, said his administration would continue to prioritize infrastructure even as there are so many other things competing for limited resources. “I have approved the sum of 10 billion Naira for an Intervention fund for the upgrade of the Akanu Ibiam International Airport, Enugu. I have the assurance of the Minister of Aviation that the work will be done speedily and to the highest standards,” he said. “Even as we have many items competing for our limited resources, we will continue to prioritize infrastructure investments in every part of the country. It is our responsibility to ensure Nigeria’s infrastructure is fixed; we will keep doing this.”